<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573531>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—An adult male Artibeus fraterculus from Bosque Protector Cerro Blanco, Guayas, Ecuador. Photograph by Jaime A. Salas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573531/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573537>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of the skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult male of Artibeus fraterculus (MUSM [Museo de Historia Natural San Marcos] 24623) from Coina, Otuzco, La Libertad, Peru. Greatest length of skull is 26.5 mm. Photographs by Víctor Pacheco." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573537/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573535>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Geographic distribution of Artibeus fraterculus redrawn by Christian Loaiza from Marques-Aguiar (2008)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573535/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

